{
  "answer": "**In Manusmṛti 9.3**, the text states the precise rule on a woman's dependence as follows: her father protects her in childhood, her husband protects her in youth, and her sons protect her in old age; a woman is never fit for independence.[^1]\n\nThis verse is part of a broader discussion in Chapter 9 on the laws of union and separation between men and women abiding in Dharma, emphasizing the need for constant male protection over women across life stages.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, [paragraph](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/09/translation/#p-233021).\n\n[^2]: Manu, *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 9, [full chapter](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/09/translation/).",
